FuncDef: The display access-user command displays information about online users (including access users and administrators). The display access-user command displays information about online users (including access users and administrators).
CLIs: display access-user access-type { admin [ ftp | ssh | telnet | terminal | http ] } [ username <user-name> ]
display access-user authentication-mode { ldap | all | hwtacacs | local | radius }
display access-user access-type { admin [ ftp | ssh | telnet | terminal | http | md-cli | snmp ] } [ username <user-name> ]
display access-user [ domain <domain-name> | ip-address <ip-address> [ vpn-instance <vpn-instance-name> ] | ipv6-address <ipv6-address> ] [ detail ]
display access-user [ domain <domain-name> | ip-address <ip-address> [ vpn-instance <vpn-instance-name> ] ] [ detail ]

ParaDef.Info:
Displays information about all users.
-

Displays information about HWTACACS authentication users.
-

Displays information about LDAP authentication users.
-

Displays information about Local authentication users.
-

Displays information about RADIUS authentication users.
-

Displays detailed information.
-

Displays information about the user with a user name.
The value must be an existing user name and is case sensitive.

Displays information about users using a specified authentication mode.
-

Displays information about the administrators using the specified authentication mode.
-

Indicates FTP users.
-

Indicates SSH users.
-

Indicates Telnet users.
-

Indicates terminal users.
-

Indicates HTTP authentication users.
-

Displays information about users connecting to a specified LPU.
The service scheme must already exist.

Displays user information with the specified user index. If this parameter is specified, detailed information about the user is displayed.
The user index must exist.

Displays information about users using a specified authentication mode.
-

Indicates the MD-CLI user.
-

Indicates SNMP users.
-

Displays information about users in a specified domain.
The value is a string of 1 to 64 case-sensitive characters, and cannot contain spaces.

Displays information about the user with a specified IP address.
The value is in dotted decimal notation.

Indicates the name of a VPN instance to which the specified IP address belongs.
The VPN instance must exist.

Displays information about the user with a specified IPv6 address.

 NOTE: This parameter is supported only on the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6860-SAN, CE6866K, CE6866, CE6860-HAM, CE6855-48XS8CQ, CE6885-SAN, CE8850-SAN, CE8855, CE8851-32CQ4BQ, CE8851K, CE8851-32CQ8DQ-P, CE8850-HAM, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K, CE6820S, CE6885, CE6885-T, CE6885-LL (standard forwarding mode) and CE6863E-48S8CQ.
The value is a 32-digit hexadecimal number, in the format of X:X:X:X:X:X:X:X.

Specifies a slot ID.

 NOTE: This parameter is supported only on the CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K and CE6820S.
The value is an integer.

Examples: <HUAWEI> display access-user access-type admin username huawei
ExtraInfo: This command displays information about user sessions on the device.
